On Monday I had the COVID vaccination. I noticed no side effects on Tuesday other than tenderness at the injection site. On Wednesday, I noticed light bruising up and down my arms. Thursday morning around 10 AM, I started to have side effect - some so severe they must be documented. At 10 AM, I felt lightheaded and had brain fog. By noon my head was pounding with a headache followed by an upset stomach. At 2 PM things started getting bad and continued to worse. It was not the headache or stomach that need to be noted but a sudden and severe onset of depression and anxiety. - Depression like I have not felt in years when I was at my worst. Throughout the day the depression worsened and by 7 PM, I was unable to stop crying and was overwhelmed with anxiety and  PTSD panic attacks. While I have the training to understand  this is temporary, - I am very worried about what I?m feeling , because there was no warning or mention of this side effect. I have the resources needed for this but people that are more fragile need to prepare for the sudden o set of critical/ debilitating depression.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the vaccine at 9AM on March 1st in my right arm.  Everything was fine until 3 PM when my right arm started swelling.  I ran a temperature of 100.1, had fatigue and a headache, in addition to aches and pains.  By Tuesday morning my right arm from the injection site to the elbow was twice it's normal size.  My chest and underarm area were both significantly swollen. I had an 8:30 AM appointment on Tuesday with an allergist who advised me to take Benadryl, which I did. By Wednesday, my chest and abdominal area were both swollen.  I had a lymphedema therapy appointment because I have lymphedema on my left side due to node removal. The therapist measured both arms and they were both swollen, including my chest and abdomen.  The therapist advised me to see my oncologist as swelling in the Right Arm, (where i received the shot) was normal for COVID shots, but she could not explain the swelling in the chest or abdomen.  Other than that my lymphatic system was working overtime. I called my oncologist on Thursday March 4, and they fit me in.  Doctor examined me and he couldn't explain to me why I was swelling up the way I was.  He has only seen arm swelling in his breast cancer patients. He is referring me to get a PET scan and advised me to see a breast surgeon as maybe the surgeon would know more about the lymph nodes.
OTHER_MEDS: I didn't take anything the morning of the vaccine, but here are my current medications: Tamoxifen Albuteral Sulfate Singulair Prilosec Zyrtec Multi-Vitamin Vitamin D
HISTORY: Asthma Hay Fever prior Breast Cancer

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient was given a covid vaccine on 3/4/21 at approximately 5:40pm.  The administration went well according to the patient.  After approximately 10 minutes, while the patient was sitting in the post vaccination area, he appeared to be pale looking to the imx RPh.  The pharmacist asked him how he was doing, he replied "I am doing so-so".  The RPh got up to check on him further when the patient fell to the floor.  The RPh rolled him on his back, got him in a comfortable position,  and elevated his legs.  RPh applied gauze to a cut in his lip, and with the immediate assistance of the health screener, applied cold compress to his neck and forehead.  Patient experienced faintness and sweaty skin only.  Patient did not show any other symptoms.  After about15 minutes, patient said he felt like himself again, and wanted to sit up in a chair.  The RPh assisted him into a chair, where he sat for 5 minutes.  At the request of the patient, he wanted to go home.  RPh escorted patient to his car and watched him get inside safely.  1 hour later, RPh followed up with a phone call to the patient and he was on his way to an urgent care clinic to get a possible stitch for his lip.
PRIOR_VAX: Patient has occasional syncope with vaccines in the past

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had a pink smear in the shape of 2 connected ovals that extended down below the injection site to my elbow.  It was pink like Pepto Bismol pink. Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA,  1st evening (Sat the 6th) very sore to touch, 2nd day Red & swelling & knot began & hurt all the time, Following days Redness & swelling and knot grew until red was a couple inches large, by Tues the 9th while getting a blood test to check metal levels from hip replacement the nurse commented on how red and swollen the arm was & that she could see the knot.  It kept growing  & I had itching in hands & side too.  Began cold pack.  Redness grew to 2x3" & red was no longer a circle.  Thurs the 18th red was 4x5" oval.  Felt like a bee sting all the time.  Area felt warm. Fri 19th to Dr & prescribed 5 day Cephalexin in case infection as I have 2 artificial hips.  Redness decreased, but swelling still there.  Redness grew & decreased and grew.  Finally on the 25th it seemed more like what you would expect if you just received the vaccination.  Coldpacks may reduce swelling & showers increase redness. March 1st I had a cytoscope to check for bladder infection & was OK.  Given one antibiotic pill.  Arm still felt like bee sting.  Today, Thursday is just a bit of redness, still a small knot, & a visible swelling.  All much less.  An ache in my arm, but may be orthopedic related? as I have had a broken arm there years ago.  It's much better, but still not back to normal.
LAB_DATA: Just the antibiotics given the 19th of February -just one day shy of 2 wk after the vaccination

The patient's past medical history included drug rash (gets rashes from other medications). Previously administered products included shingrix (1st dose received at the end of Spring in 2020). Concurrent medical conditions included heart rate low.   On 23rd December 2020, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On 23rd December 2020, less than a day after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced pain in arm and drug dose administration interval too long. On 24th December 2020, the patient experienced swelling arm, erythema of extremities, induration and tingling skin. On 25th December 2020, the patient experienced injection site rash, rash, itchy rash and red rash. On 26th December 2020, the patient experienced blister and discouragement. On 27th December 2020, the patient experienced ankle swelling. The patient was treated with benadryl (nos) (Benadryl Cream). On 28th December 2020, the outcome of the ankle swelling was recovered/resolved. On an unknown date, the outcome of the injection site rash, pain in arm, swelling arm, erythema of extremities, induration, rash, tingling skin, itchy rash, red rash, blister, discouragement and drug dose administration interval too long were unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the injection site rash, pain in arm, swelling arm, erythema of extremities, induration, rash, tingling skin, itchy rash, red rash, blister, discouragement and ankle swelling to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were reported as follows: The patient was fine at night of vaccination however, her left arm was sore to the touch for days. On next day after vaccination arm became red, swollen and hard. On night of 26th December 2020, she was felt tingly on her skin and chest. On Christmas morning (25th December 2020) and she had a rash on her abdomen so she used extra strength Benadryl cream and she felt better. By lunch that day she could felt the rash moving around her waist so she used more Benadryl cream. She then felt it on her thighs with itching and the rash got on both her legs past her knees on her arms and hands. On 26th December 2020, rash looked like was going to blister on her left wrist but she ate well, drank water and used more lotion and cream and it never got worse and it got better. She could feel the rash running under her skin in her nerve endings. The patient had low heart rate and is not immunocompromised and felt that she was very healthy which was why she was surprised she got a rash. The patient claimed that she first saw the rash under the band aid at the injection site on her left arm, however, band aids will bother her sometimes. On 25th December 2020,  rash started on the left side and a little on the left breast and traveled up onto the left nipple area and traveled across the abdomen down the left thigh, then moved to the waistband area and in her belly button and on her side and back and by the afternoon the rash looked like sunburn. On 26th December 2020, rash bothered her and it was unnerving and on the inside of her arms it looked like blisters however on next day it was good. On 27th December 2020, she was baking and she had a swollen ankle on the right side which dissipated by next day. The reporter stated that swelling could be related to a lack of water, her age and being so busy on that Sunday. The reporter consented to follow up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Dizziness; felt like I was being pushed against the wall /  I couldn't walk straight and had to cling to something / my balance was off/ falling over to left side; didn't get a lot of sleep; arm felt sore / hurt to lift it up; hurt to lift it up; tight muscles in the upper shoulder area; didn't get a lot of sleep, got up and didn't feel real good; couldn't walk straight; didn't feel real good; had fever; This case was reported by a consumer and described the occurrence of dizziness in a 76-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) (batch number J454X, expiry date 4th October 2022) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included back pain and muscle tightness. Previously administered products included Shingrix with an associated reaction of pain in extremity (1st dose received in November 2020, for tolerance refer case US2021AMR025675).   On 28th January 2021, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. In January 2021, less than a day after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced fever, muscle tightness, sleeplessness, walking difficulty and malaise. On 28th January 2021, the patient experienced restlessness, pain in arm and pain upon movement. On 30th January 2021, the patient experienced dizziness and balance disorder. On an unknown date, the outcome of the dizziness, balance disorder, restlessness, fever, pain in arm and malaise were recovered/resolved and the outcome of the pain upon movement, muscle tightness, sleeplessness and walking difficulty were unknown.   The reporter considered the dizziness, balance disorder, restlessness, fever, pain in arm, pain upon movement, muscle tightness, sleeplessness, walking difficulty and malaise to be possibly related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: This case was reported by patient herself. The patient did not have a history of reaction to any previous vaccines. The patient received 2nd dose of Shingrix and a day after she experienced dizziness, and falling over to left side. The patient had to support or she would have gone down. On the night of vaccination, the patient's arm felt sore, hurt to lift it up but otherwise felt fine. She had restless night that night, had fever and it was 0.9 degrees over normal. She was up for a while, did not get a lot of sleep, got up and did not feel very good. She felt like, she needed more sleep. She felt fine after sitting down on toilet but when she looked out and things did not look right, so she stood up and just went to her left up against the wall. She managed to walk over, hung on to door and managed to walk to the sink. It just felt like she was being pushed against the wall. She had no history of this happening before. One time she had dizzy spell from a new blood pressure medication, but that was totally different, that felt like room was spinning. With this the patient could not walk straight and had to cling to something, like her balance was off. The patient had a history of issues with back and tight muscles but now she felt like she had tight muscles in the upper shoulder area. She stated she sat on bed for 10 minutes or so, walked out to the family room with husband supporting her on the left, husband used a massager to work on muscles of neck and shoulder and after another 20 minutes or so, she was able to walk around with support. Then within an hour the symptoms were resolved. The reporter thought it was possible that these reactions related to the vaccination since the patient just had the shot the day before it could have something to do with it. The reporter consented to follow up with her as well as with her pharmacist who administered the vaccine. The patient had not yet discussed symptoms with her physician and was referred to her physician for further evaluation and discussion. This case had been linked with US2021025187 and US202102517, reported by same reporter.; Sender's Comments:  US-GLAXOSMITHKLINE-US2021025187:same reporter US-GLAXOSMITHKLINE-US2021AMR025675:same reporter

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had no reaction to the first shot , except sore arm for one day.  After the 2nd shot, the next day I developed a high fever (103) and chills.  I called urgent care that evening to see how to bring the fever down.  They told me that was my body building antibodies.  The fever "broke" later that night.  I never have gotten rid of the chills.  I did not see a doctor for this reaction. During this time, not exactly sure of the dates, the cardiologist started me on a new medicine - Verapamil.   I thought the chills might be from the medicine.  She reduced the dosage due to low heart rate, and I'm still taking the medicine.   I now have a rash on my side and on my left thigh, which is blotchy, red, and itchy.  I do not know if these reactions are from the medicine or from the vaccine, but I suspect it is the Moderna vaccine.  The chills are mostly centered in my legs.  They are not letting up.  I have not seen my doctor about the rash yet.  I have had the rash for a couple of weeks, trying to get rid of it myself.
OTHER_MEDS: Losartan, Albuteral inhaler, methimazole, Vitamin B complex, VitaminD, pravastatin, Krill Oi, verapamil

On 21 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number: 029L20A), intramuscularly for the prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 15 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their second planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number: 004M20A), into the arm for the prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On an unknown date in Feb 2021, the patient experienced sore arm, and feels that did not received the full vaccine. The patient noticed that the nurse who administered her the vaccine squeezed the arm before giving the vaccine, and it seems that the syringe did not enter to the muscle but entered to the fat. The patient states that, between the two doses, took an antibody test, with a negative result. The patient inquires if she can take another antibody test and if she can receive a third dose to ensure more protection. No treatment information was provided.  Action taken with second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not applicable. SYMPTOM_TEXT: blurred vision; fuzzy hearing; nausea; pain in left arm; snoring sound; fainted; did not feel well; she jerked in motion in arms and leg x 3; Initial information received on 28-Oct-2020 regarding an unsolicited valid serious case received from a other health professional.   This case involves a 17 year old female patient who fainted (syncope), had blurred vision (vision blurred), fuzzy hearing (Hypoacusis), nausea, did not feel well (malaise), she jerked in motion in arms and leg x 3 (dyskinesia), had pain in left arm (pain in extremity) and had snoring, after she received vaccines DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE [ADACEL] and MENINGOCOCCAL A-C-Y-W135 (D CONJ) VACCINE [MENACTRA].  The patient had no medical history, concomitant disease or risk factor.  Medical treatment, vaccination, concomitant medication and family history were not provided.  On 28-Oct-2020, the patient received a dose of suspect MENINGOCOCCAL A-C-Y-W135 (D CONJ) VACCINE (lot number and expiry date: not reported) via an unknown route in the left arm for prophylactic vaccination.  On 28-Oct-2020, the patient received a dose of suspect DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE (lot number and expiry date: not reported) via an unknown route at an unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination.  On 28-Oct-2020, reported as within 5 minutes of vaccination, the patient developed a serious feeling of unwell (malaise), fainted (syncope) and while coming out she jerked in motion in arms and leg x 3 (dyskinesia) and had non-serious event of snoring sounds, following the administration of MENINGOCOCCAL A-C-Y-W135 (D CONJ) VACCINE and DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE. These events (except snoring) were assessed as medically significant.  On 28-Oct-2020, soon after coming out of first syncope, the patient said she was ok and then she fainted again. She came out of this second fainting episode with serious events of blurred vision (vision blurred), fuzzy hearing (feeling abnormal) and nausea (unknown latency) following the administration of MENINGOCOCCAL A-C-Y-W135 (D CONJ) VACCINE and DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE. These events were also assessed as medically significant.  On an unknown date, the patient also reported a non-serious pain in left arm (pain in extremity) (unknown latency) following the administration of MENINGOCOCCAL A-C-Y-W135 (D CONJ) VACCINE and DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE.  It is unknown if patient's physician provided consent to be contacted It is unknown if the patient experienced any additional symptoms/events.  There were no lab data/results available.  It was not reported if the patient received a corrective treatment.  At the time of reporting, the outcome of all events were reported as unknown.; Sender's Comments: This case involves 17 year old female patient who had syncope, vision blurred, hearing abnormality, nausea, malaise, dyskinesia, pain in extremity and snoring, after vaccination with ADACEL and MENACTRA. The time to onset is compatible. Additional information regarding patient's medical history, condition at the time of vaccination, lab data excluding other etiologies would be needed for complete assessment of the case. Based upon the reported information, the role of an individual vaccines cannot be assessed.

I received vaccine. Noted at the 30 minute post wait vaccine site feeling a very slight like it was hard to take a deep breath 15 minutes after receiving the vaccine. I took my pulse. It was 90. I did not tell the  medical monitor people. My husband drove me home after the 30 minute watch period was up. At 1:15pm I gave myself an albuterol neb to. Post tx home pulse ox was 95% pulse 96. No n/v, no itching. Breathing felt improved . I did a home peak flow reading which was 240. My personal best baseline is 350. I auscultated my anterior chest. Diminished, clear, no wheezing. I sat calmly. My husband noticed the left side of my face was mildly swollen. Amazing! For him to notice! it was very slight around cheek bone to jawline. I sent him to get otc Benadryl. I took 25 mg po . At 2:20 pm Pam was 300 p02 sat 98% pulse 96. Lips felt tingling, no swelling. Speech clear. Swallowing intact Drank water, low sodium soup. 3:30 pm did another albuterol next. Sat 95% after neb . Pulse 89. 20 minutes post neb peak flow reading 320. Started feeling chills. Temp outside a nice seventy degree day. Wrapped self 6 blankets,winter hoody fleece, heating pad and finally fell asleep. Family watched me sleep. Woke up 7pm. Still felt cold. Had fluids, urinated, breathing ok. Went back to sleep. 11 pm woke up, peak flow 300, did neb, took Benadryl wore my cpap machine and went to bed till today.

First vaccine I could feel the vaccine go into my body and down into my legs. It was a very strange sensation. I felt very fatigued 30 min after the vaccine but ignored it because it was not normal to have symptoms after the first vaccine. That night i did feel a litlle bit of swelling in my lips that continued into the next day but it was not severe. The muscle aches, joint pain and allodynia the 2nd day were so severe I don't really remember any other symptoms i may have had. I took Benadryl and Tylenol and slept for 2 days straight. After the 1st vaccine I did have shortness of breath for about 3 days post. Then I received the 2nd vaccine, I did not feel it go in this time. About 30 min after the second vaccine I felt very fatigued. About an hour later I started to feel slight swelling in my lips that increased and around 2 1/2 hours my eyes and lips were noticeably swollen and I was flushed. My husband noticed my ears and cheeks were bright red.   I felt my heart racing and took my pulse it was around 120. I felt dizzy and like there was a lump in my throat.   I requested an appointment via video call from  the emergency line.  I  didn't feel like I was having trouble breathing and stayed calm, my pulse went down to 100 after about 20 min. while waiting for my video call. I spoke to the doctor and they recommended going to the ER. I asked since the pulse went down and it felt like I was slowly reacting, if I could try taking Benadryl and see how I felt. She said that was ok but if I felt any difficulty breathing to go to  the ER right away. I took 50 mg of Benadryl and felt better and rested. The next morning lips and eyes were swollen again but a little worse. Difficulty swallowing persisted as well as severe muscle pain, joint pain, and allodynia.  The symptoms were worse with 2nd vaccine. Noticed shortness of breath just walking up and down steps. These symptoms lasted a little bit longer.  4 days after the vaccine I noticed  the lip swelling was not getting better so I called my PCP. He recommended taking the next 2 days off , rest with benadryl and tylenol. I listened and felt good enough to go into work. It is now 4 weeks since i had the vaccine and i am still experiencing  some symptoms that seem to be in relation to after i eat. That includes lip swelling, tightness in the muscles around my throat (feel as if they are strained), stomach burning, indigestion, heartburn.  Called PCP again who recommended I see an allergist/immunologist.
LAB_DATA: Waiting to see allergist and immunologist on the 15th.

The patient was diagnosed with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) exacerbation and pneumonia. He additionally suffered from sensorineural hearing loss and varicella-like rash. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient's symptoms resulted in physical limitations not present prior to the vaccination. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), he suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the events was not recovered. The relatedness between the events and zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) was related. SYMPTOM_TEXT: he fell; bumped his head; This case was reported by a nurse via other manufacturer and described the occurrence of fall in a 72-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included partial gastrectomy (from July 2016) and stroke (in 2015). Previously administered products included Flu vaccine with an associated reaction of no adverse event (kind of vaccine with no reaction.), Hepatitis vaccine with an associated reaction of no adverse event (kind of vaccine with no reaction) and Shingrix with an associated reaction of nasopharyngitis (1st dose received on unknown date and also had clammy, diaphoretic, high blood sugar and many more, refer case US2021AMR032604). Concurrent medical conditions included dementia, diabetes (since from 2005) and allergy nos.   On an unknown date, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On an unknown date, less than a year after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced fall and local swelling. On an unknown date, the outcome of the fall and local swelling were unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the fall and local swelling to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were reported as follows: This case was reported by patient's spouse. The age at vaccination was not reported but it could be 71 or 72 years old. The patient was allergic to various things and would had to clear patient's throat. The patient has not had the reaction in the past to the vaccines received and he had every kind of vaccine with no reaction. The patient did not have the reaction to the Flu or Hepatitis vaccines. The Shingrix was for 2 doses and the patient decided to get the 2nd dose. The patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix and the patient fell and bumped his head with that reaction. The reporter could tried giving the patient an extran blood pressure pill. The patient did not have NDC, lot or expiry to provide. The reporter tried to saw if there were components that match up but she did not see any components that were the same. The reporter consented to follow up.; Sender's Comments:  US-GLAXOSMITHKLINE-US2021AMR032604:Same patient, same reporter, same product, different dose (2nd dose)
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Partial gastrectomy (from July 2016); Stroke (in 2015)

thrush / felt like a terrible poison ivy on her back, arms, shoulders to her elbow on both sides of her body / thrush went all the way up to the hairline and to her butt; soreness when she would roll over when sleeping; scabs; swelling of the arm; couldn't sleep; sore arm; digging at the thrush because it felt like sand under the skin / itch; was miserable/  felt like sand under the skin; terrible poison ivy on back, arm, shoulder to elbow on both side of body; ill with COPD; coughing badly; illness; fever; throwing up; diarrhea; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease in a 78-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   Previously administered products included Zostavax (received vaccine years ago). Concomitant products included methylprednisolone.   In September 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix. In December 2020, between 2 and 4 months after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, cough and illness. On an unknown date, the patient experienced thrush, general body pain, scab, fever, vomiting, diarrhea, swelling arm, difficulty sleeping, pain in arm, pruritus, feeling miserable and poison ivy rash. On an unknown date, the outcome of the chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, cough, illness, thrush and scab were not recovered/not resolved and the outcome of the general body pain, fever, vomiting, diarrhea, swelling arm, difficulty sleeping, pain in arm, pruritus, feeling miserable and poison ivy rash were recovered/resolved.  It was unknown if the reporter considered the chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, cough, illness, thrush, general body pain, scab, fever, vomiting, diarrhea, swelling arm, difficulty sleeping, pain in arm, pruritus, feeling miserable and poison ivy rash to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The reporter was reported for herself. The age at vaccination was not reported. The patient received 1st dose of Shingrix in the left arm. The reporter stated that, few days after vaccination, had sore arm, swelling of the arm and soreness when would roll over when sleeping. A few days later experienced diarrhea, throwing up, fever which lasted 3 days. The patient described as thrush which felt like a terrible poison ivy on her back, arms, shoulders to her elbow on both sides of her body. The patient would wake up at night digging at the thrush because it felt like sand under the skin and would dig the head off and still had scabs where she dug so badly. The thrush went all the way up to the hairline and to her butt where the patient sat and was miserable. The reporter stated that, the only symptom that remains today was thrush. The reporter did mention at the end of the conversation that she was currently ill with COPD and she was coughing badly.  She said that her illness started 2 weeks ago and it was a seasonal thing for her. The physician prescribed medication for the itch because she could not sleep. The patient was advised by her physician to not get the second dose of Shingrix. The reporter consented to follow up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Nurse notified by Client  Client reports having a sore throat At 4:21 Client report a soreness and tightness in her throat, difficulty swallowing, and headache   Vitals taken: O sat 98, Pulse 88 , BP 170/110 ( left arm),  At 4:22 BP taken again on opposite arm (right arm 183/119) At 4:23 EMT assessed client breathing with stethoscope . Airway and breathing Clear  At 4:26 Vitals taken : BP 160/110, O Sat 98, Pulse 86, No wheezing, No difficulty breathing At 4:29 EMT  speaks with the dispatcher for an ambulance EMT reports client is alert and oriented x 4 and has no difficulty breathing Client reports  no difficulty swallowing Client wanted to be transported because of the high blood pressure reading . She has no history of high blood pressure Client states her previous BP reading was not normal. She recently had a check up with her physician  At 4:37 Client sat outside for some air and is drinking water Client reports that she feels better At 4:38 BP taken: BP 158/90  Client states that she wants the ambulance paramedics to check her heart on the EKG and will make a decision about being transported EMT  called again to check the current location of the ambulance. Ambulance in route on  Campus At 4:45 Client reports no tightness in her throat, and no headache Vitals taken: O Sat 96, Pulse 70  Client previously mentioned that she was anticipating her son who is allergic to bees to have a reaction and not herself. She also states that her husband will be so angry about this since he didn?t want them to get the Covid vaccine. She also mentioned traffic was really bad getting to the resource center building At 4:55 EMT assessed vitals: BP 132/ 92   At 5:04 Ambulance arrives  Client reports feeling better  Paramedics assess client  No wheezing, No Shortness of Breath, No chest pain, No nausea Client reports her physical was last week and no issues with Blood pressure  At 5:08 Vitals taken on monitor : BP 189/99, Pulse 82, O Sat 99   Manually BP taken by paramedic BP 190/78 At 5:13 Paramedic checks heart reading on the monitor/ EKG in the ambulance At 5:24 Paramedics report No abnormal readings found on the heart monitor / EKG Client decided not to be transported and feels well enough to drive home

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got my Pfizer first dose today and it was fine at first, but four hours later I was slammed with incredible arm and shoulder pain. I have a really high pain tolerance (tore my meniscus 3x with no surgery or pain meds, wasn't too bad) and I'm 24F, not on any medications. I keep reading that sore arms are common, but this is a 6/7 on the pain scale. Putting on joggers was excruciating and I almost vomited. I can't even bring a glass to my mouth with that arm. Even laying as still as possible hurts. I cannot lift my arm past my pelvis and my shoulder is immobile. I feel nauseous when I move it.  I haven't seen this experience anywhere so I am puzzled... I'm fully vaccinated w/ everything else and the closest to this was the tetanus shot, which hurt but not like - this - level of pain. I'm getting a bit concerned that the person who did it (in a hundred car drive thru) missed the deltoid and shot it into my shoulder?? It's VERY high on my arm. I believe in this vax 100% but I can't believe the pain I'm having and why it's not mentioned anywhere.  Like I am so so grateful for this vax and am in awe of the science -- and everyone should get it   -- but I just don't understand why I'm in literal excruciating pain :( Moving it even slightly feel like I'm ripping it from the bone.   It?s now been 20 hours and the pain is worse than ever, even breathing, sneezing or bending over causes searing pain.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had no immediate reactions to the vaccine. About an hour after my injection I developed a low grade headache. The next day, 2/26, I woke at 7am with a headache still. The headache and fatigue worsened through the day (2/26/21).  Around 3:00pm I started experiencing waves of dizziness. By 4pm I had begun experiencing temporary loss of feeling in  various body parts. Each part's loss of feeling came and went separately and lasted about 2-5 minutes each. I experienced this in my left facial cheek, both wrists and hands, and my right hip. I had a coworker drive me home and by 5pm I had a migraine with severe sinus/head pressure and a fever of 99.4. My average resting body temperature is 97.4. I slept from 6:00pm friday till 10:30am on Saturday (2/27). When I woke I still had a headache, but no longer a migraine.  I spent 2/27 dizzy, weak, and achy but no more episodes of lack of feeling in body parts or a fever.  I have not experienced soreness in the arm I got my injection in, but I noticed on Tuesday March 2nd that I my injection site is very swollen, red and itchy. The swelling and redness (to my knowledge) has not gotten worse or better since then, but the itching has gotten worse and the actual puncture wound is now visible since yesterday (3/4) whereas it was not visible anytime  before  that.
OTHER_MEDS: Adderall, Viibryd, Valtrex/Valacyclovir, Mirena IUD, Iron supplement, B complex supplement, D3 supplement,

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had severe COVID and was hospitalized on Dec 7,  I was in hospital (non ICU setting) for 5 days and had O2, remdisiver and dethemethzone IV.  I recovered fully, and have felt very good since mid January.  My reaction after my 1st dose of vaccine on Feb 25  started 20 hours after shot.  Worsened through the day and I got sicker at 24-36 hours, and then stayed in bed another day.  Symptoms were identical to my bout with COVID:  chills (no fever),  nausea, aches in joints and muscles, fatigue.  They were quite significant==I could not be out of bed.  As it went along I also developed the feeling in my chest like COVID--tough to take deep breath, chest hurt---but my O2 readings were fine.   Recovered after 48 hours, People who have had COVID should be aware that they will have a significant response to the vaccine on the 1st does.  I am questioning having a second dose I have not reported this to my doctor
Right sided Bell's Palsy

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Daughter calling to ask about side effects of COVID vaccine? She said her 83 yr old dad got the COVID- 19 yesterday and overnight he became confused, had severe weakness, couldn't get out of bed, and became feverish.  She said mom said they both got first dose of COVID vaccine yesterday around noon- then last night he started to feel unwell. Around 2am- her mom said her dad- became very weak, couldn't get out of bed, confused, started coughing, he had chills, felt feverish. She said so concerning by 4am her mom called EMS who came and took him to the Medical Center.   She said he had pretty severe case of COVID in December that he need hospitalized for-she said  he as really weak, foggy headed at that time, kind of out of his mind- she said was told that is how he was acting last night.   After being seen in ED and getting put on some fluids and then antibiotics he now seems to be acting more like himself. They hydrated- have some concerns about possible pneumonia dx so they started him on antibiotics- was told this might be due to his rxn post + COVID vaccine - which is what prompted her to call today.   He is supposed to follow up with his PCP doctor.  He seemed better when he got home this morning- she said just left him a little bit ago after eating early lunch with him. She is not sure if getting him hydrated & sent home with antibiotics is what helped or just time since now about 24 hours post vaccination dose.  Confirmed he has had no prior rxn to any other vaccines in the past.
HISTORY: stroke years ago, also takes BP & cholesterol medications

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 2 days after receiving the second dose I started experiencing redness and pain at the injection site. It was also warm to the touch. It was about almost 2 in in diameter. It got worse on the next day and it slowly started getting better, it went away in about 4 days. Then I had a gallbladder surgery that was scheduled on 01/29/2021. On 02/03/2021 I was feeling excruciating pain that I believe it was related to the gallbladder surgery. I went to the ER, the same hospital where I got the vaccine at and they ran a lot of tests on me, blood work, CT scans, ultrasounds and they told me my D Dimer was elevated: 2371. They attributed it to my recent surgery and told me to FU with my PCP. When I FU'd with my PCP Dr., she requested new blood work and this time my D Dimer was even higher than the results at the ED: 2610. That was on 03/01/2021. She is trying to get me in the Clinic she is concerned about cancer. I think it might be something regarding the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: Blood work, 2 Ct Scans (one was of my chest and it showed and isolated mildly and enlarged nodular density in the anterior media sternum at the level of the thoracic endlet. This may be related to an atopic thyroid tissue or a mildly enlarged lymph node), Ultrasound at Hospital - Blood Work with my PCP Dr.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin C, D, Prozac, Zyrtec, Topamax

It is 4 days after reaction appeared, and the inflammation and swollenness has now subsided. The location remains itchy, no more fever.

These continued until apx 24 hours later when additional mental fog set it, difficulty focusing attention, lethargy, trouble walking, dizziness then brief loss of consciousness occurred, extreme difficulty staying awake. I was taken to the emergency room where additional tests were done due to "stroke- like" symptoms.  Tests were okay with hospital staff reporting that likely/only known cause was the COVID  vaccine given the day before. Symptoms have gradually reduced but occasional mental fog, occasional dizzy spells & chronic fatigue persist.

The adolescent and mother misrepresented patients age at time of vaccination. At an outreach clinic one dose of Pfizer was remaining. Vaccine coordinator for site/office asked if this individual could receive a the last dose to exhaust and not have a wastage. The coordinator was informed they could as long as the person was at least 16 y/o old.  He was reported as being 16 so mother brought him to site to receive vaccination. Before administering the vaccinator asked patient if he had just turned 16 and he reported "yes".  On the consent form his birthday was clearly written. Which would have made him 16 at time of administration.  Vaccine was given and individual had no issues on site.  While trying to document in patients online/electronic shot record staff could not locate him under the date of birth written and verified by mother and patient.  It was later verified by mother that his year was 2006 and not 2005. State immunization MD notified and was informed to administer the second dose when the 21 days is due and to file a Vaers report since adolescent was under 16.

Patient received vaccine at 12:01, she stated that approximately 12:30  she noticed her right palm felt itchy and she noticed red bumps on the inside of her right wrist.   She reported the symptoms to the onsite paramedics.  She stated that she was placed on a stretcher and given 60 mg of liquid benadryl by the paramedics.   She stated she started feeling dizzy, but after 3 minutes the dizziness resolved.  She stated that soon after that the itchy right palm resolved, and the red spots on her right wrist diminished.  She stated the paramedics took her blood pressure, 150/100 and placed her on oxygen. Flare up throughout the body due to covid vaccination; Flare up throughout the body due to winter; Allergic to Enbrel; Asthma flare-up; Sinus infection; Bronchitis; Covid 19 vaccine route of administration: Endocervical; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable healthcare professional, based on the information received by Pfizer from agency (manufacturer control number: US-AMGEN-USASP2020193179), license party for etanercept (ENBREL).  This spontaneous report (USASP2020193179) was reported to agency on 25/NOV/2020 by an other health professional and involves a 41-year-old female patient who was allergic to Enbrel [PT: drug hypersensitivity], asthma flare-up [PT: asthma], sinus infection [PT: sinusitis], and bronchitis [PT: bronchitis] while receiving Otezla and Enbrel. No historical medical condition was reported. The patient's current medical condition included psoriatic arthropathy, cough, disease of upper respiratory tract, herpesviral (herpes simplex), irritable bowel syndrome, lupus erythematosus, infection of the skin, migraine, oligomenorrhea, personal history of other diseases of psoriasis, unspecified skin changes and asthma. The patient had allergic to Arava (Leflunomide), cimzia prefl kit (certolizumab pegol), Depo-Medrol (Methylprednisolone Acetate), Humira (Adalimumab), lidocaine, methotrexate, stelara (Ustekinumab), tetracycline, and allergic to Latex gloves and secure glove. The patient's concomitant medications included albuterol [salbutamol], benzonatate, Cymbalta (duloxetine hydrochloride), fexofenadine, multivitamin [vitamins nos], thyroid, and prednisone, Wal Zyr (cetirizine hydrochloride) and amoxicillin and potassium clavulanate. No co-suspect medications were reported. The patient began Otezla on 15/JUN/2016 and Enbrel on an unknown date. First dose in left arm with significant pain and swelling in left axillary lymph node 6 days after vaccine. This still hurts 6 weeks later.  Second dose I chose to have it in my other arm since first arm still hurt.  Same problem. Lymph node swelling in right axillary lymph node the next day.  Problem: This side effect has not been widely communicated. I did not know that this was a side effect and did not connect it to the vaccine the first time because it happened 6 days after my vaccination date. So, this caused me to go to two doctors. The first doctor was online and did not know the problem but suspected that I could have a DVT. She did not know that this was a side effect. So, she sent me to an in person doctor who recognized that it was a vaccine side effect. Please add this side effect to your publicity to save others from having an unnecessary doctor's visit.
LAB_DATA: Two doctor's visits. No texts or labs.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received a COVID vaccination for her second dose on 3/3/21 at 1538.  She had informed the staff of the clinic that she did have a local reaction following her first dose (9days later) that she saw her PCP for. This was just treated with Zyrtec and no further intervention.  At 25 minutes following her second dose PA noticed that the patient appeared flushed.  He checked with the patient and she said she was ok.  A few minutes later noticed the patient was even more flushed.  At that time went and evaluated the patient - her BP was elevated 150/94 HR of 112 ad Pulse ox of 96%.  The patient reported feeling different than how she felt after her previous injection.  Clinic team offered for patient to be transferred to ER for further evaluation if she would like which the patient accepted.  She was transferred to ER via wheelchair in less than 5 minutes in stable condition with mild nausea.  She was cared for in ER by Dr.  Patient reported feeling tired and 'heavy' in the ER.  Dr evaluation found a generally healthy patient with a non-toxic appearance  Lungs were clear and no obvious signs of swelling or other signs of an immediate allergic reaction.  Patient was given oral diphenhydramine and observed until she felt comfortable going home.  Discharged from ER at 1733
OTHER_MEDS: Ibuprofen 600mg every 6 hours, a medication for acid reflux - name unknown.  Patient did take Zyrtec following her 1st dose of the Moderna vaccine due to a delayed local reaction.
HISTORY: Obesity, patient self reports issues with anxiety though not a listed health condition on her medical record.

3/3/21 er to hospital admission:  81 y.o. female with a history of Parkinson's in previous stroke.  The patient basically is maintained in the nursing home in this state of being bed-bound and nonverbal.  She was recently transferred to Rehab after she developed a stage IV sacral ulcer at a previous nursing home.  The patient had been seeing wound care and doing very well.  Her stage IV sacral ulcer had been healed to a stage II.  She had been gaining weight.  Unfortunately, at her wound care appointment yesterday the wound had decompensated a little bit and had started to drain some purulent material.  It also enlarged in size a little bit.  I was called yesterday afternoon and the nursing home reported the patient was not wanting to eat or drink.  Lab work showed a sodium of 170 and creatinine consistent with acute kidney injury.  She also appeared to have a urinary tract infection.  Because of her critical labs she was sent to the nursing home.  The patient was evaluated in the nursing home and then admitted to the floor.  She was given Zosyn and vancomycin and started on IV fluids.  The emergency room physician did counsel the family that the prognosis was very grim.  The patient has done reasonably well overnight.  She has been grimacing quite a bit and the family has decided they just want her kept comfortable    comfort care during admission
Patient returned early for his second dose and was vaccinated too early.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had my first COVID vaccine on 1/16/21. I had my second one on 2/5/21. On 2/9/21 I started experiencing a sharp pain in my left breast. On 2/10/21 I had sharp pain in between my shoulder blades. On 2/11/21 I noticed a small red rash-like spot in between my breast. I woke up on 2/12/21 in incredible pain on my back, so I lifted my shirt to look in the mirror and that is when I noticed a blister type rash from the middle of my back wrapping around the front of my body covering my left breast. I went to see the PA at my PCP's office. She diagnosed me with shingles. She placed me on an anti-viral medication for a week, and gabapentin (nerve medication) for a month. It has been 3 weeks today since I first began treatment and I have not fully recovered yet. My blisters dried up about a week ago, but ever since then I have been incredibly itchy, which has kept me up every night for over a week now. On 3/3/21 I called my PCP's office and they started me on Prednisone for 6 days. I am 2 days into treatment and I still have not had relief from the itching.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received Pfizer COVID19 injection at 9:57 am on March 4 at the . As is usual for any shot or IV on me, I immediately tasted something weird in my mouth. It was not as metallic tasting as usual. More plasticy. Shot did not hurt.   Was told to stay in 30 minutes waiting area.I did. The taste remained in my mouth. I left at 10:34 am feeling OK, except for weird taste.  As I drove off the parking lot, I noticed that my mouth and tongue were tingling, with worst of it on my left side.  My throat did not seem to be affected, so I continued driving. Some nasal congestion and coughing.  The tingling turned into numbness in my mouth and tongue, all the way back to top of throat.  I called my primary care doctor at 12:10 pm and left a message.  I received a call back at 2:15 pm from nurse. She told me to take Benadryl and have someone take me to Urgent Care right away to get my vitals checked. I did not take Benadryl, as CDC said it could mask anaphylactic reaction.  I called a friend and she took me . I noticed that my lymph nodes in my neck were swelling and painful.  We arrived at 2:45 pm. My vitals were checked, heart and breathing listened to and was checked briefly  for swelling in mouth and throat. There was no swelling. He said he had never heard of this tingling reaction and claimed it is just a side effect and not a serious reaction and that it would probably last a couple of days. He recommended that I watch for new symptoms and take Benadryl. That was $30. We left at 3:10.  We left. I noticed that the numbness was spreading to my lips and up the left side of face and I was getting super tired. Also, my mid to lower back started hurting a lot. I took a Benadryl.  4:30 pm still have same numbness. My eyes got super dry and itchy. My head started to hurt. Some coughing.  5:10 pm dry eye and numbness, more swollen lymph nodes and chills. Pain in calves, upper back, same on both sides.  6:38 weirdly, from the bottom of my thumb to halfway up my arm there is pain. Both arms simultaneously. Worse on the  left.  8:11 pm after bundling up and using a heating pad, plus extra heat, chills are lessened. Lymph nodes very sore in neck. Eyes are not quite as dry. Everything else is the same.  8:48 pm jaw really aches. Intestinal discomfort. Going to bed.  10:39 pm pain from jaw extended up into left ear. Upper part of throat hurts.  March 5, 2021  4:00 am. Body aches have lessened. Left arm sore at shot area.  5:45 am  eyes definitely dry, but not nearly as dry as yesterday. Numbness in mouth , tongue and face has lessened, but still uncomfortably present. Definitely worse on the left side. Little bit of tingling on the left, mostly on cheek from chin to ear. Headache gone. Lymph nodes sore and swollen .  7:00 am went on a walk. Noticed some achyness throughout body. Very tired.  10:51 am The tingling and numbness remain in my mouth, tongue and cheek up to my left eye.  Very tired. Lymph nodes still swollen and sore.
LAB_DATA: Had vitals checked and a peek into my mouth at an Urgent Care Center.

Dateline and symptoms:  03/01 Received first Moderna Covid Vaccination at 3:45 p.m... 03/02 No symptoms until 6 p.m. When blood pressure started to go up from my normal level of 116/68 to 179/82 by 10 p.m..  During this time I had what felt like mild electric currents from the left side of my chest down my left arm and into my hand.  These systems subsided around 11 p.m. and by midnight my blood pressure was almost back to normal. 03/03 Felt sluggish all day but no blood pressure problems. 03/04 Felt great all day then around 6 p.m. my blood pressure started to rise, by 9:30 p.m. it was 190/90.  At this time I started to feel like my body was shutting down, my face felt flush, and experiencing long distant vision problems, so I had my wife take me to the emergency room. At 10:00 p.m. I went to the emergency room  EKG  showed no heart problems, the blood test showed no heart problems, and after 11:30 p.m. my blood pressure started going down and I was released at 1:30 a.m..  Blood test did show high levels of Blood Urea Nitrogen 26.0, Bun/Creatinine Ratio 33.0, Aspartate Amino Tranf (AST/SGOT) 43, Alanine Aminotransferase (ALT/SGPT) 59 and Alkaline Phosphatase 189, all of which are higher than my last blood test on 10/22/20. 03/05  As of 10:30 a.m. my blood pressure is 126/62.  I feel fine except I'm very tired from not much sleep last night.  1p.m. Starting to feel some more chest and arm symptoms as described before, blood pressure now 146/66. Events happened twice, 2 days apart.

The outcome of the events, seemed drunk and his feet from the knee down, he could no longer walk and could only crawl,  just drags his feet and was also getting tired very quickly, was considered unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the information provided which includes a strong temporal association, a causal association between the reported events and the administration of the mRNA-1273 cannot be excluded. On 12-Feb-2021, approximately 2 days prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unknown) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.    The patient received his vaccine on 12-Feb-2021 and reported that his arm hurt a little for a few days. He went to urgent care where he was diagnosed with a pulmonary embolism for which he received treatment. On the evening of the same day, he again started having difficulty breathing with pain upon inhalation. He returned to urgent care and was subsequently admitted at 12:30 AM on 21-Feb-2021. That  Monday, 22-Feb-2021, a doppler ultrasound revealed a deep vein thrombosis in the left calf. Patient was treated with heparin intravenously (IV). He was discharged 22-Feb-2021.    Treatment for the event included Xarelto 20mg twice per day for two weeks and Heparin IV.    Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided/unknown.  The outcome of the events, pulmonary embolism, deep vein thrombosis and dyspnea, was considered recovering/resolving as of discharge on 22-Feb-2021. A 61-year-old female patient received their first dose of bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE; lot number: EL1283, expiry date not reported), via an unspecified route of administration on the left arm on 20Jan2021 18:45 at single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included diabetes mellitus and high BP from an unknown date and unknown if ongoing. Concomitant medications included levothyroxine, losartan potassium and sodium fluoride (CREST CAVITY PROTECTION). The patient previously took septra and experienced allergies. The patient reported that on 21Jan2021, they woke up and brushed their teeth then at 6:40am blood with large clots gushed from their right (rt) nostril. The patient went to ER and stopped bleeding after 2 hrs. On 22Jan2021, the patient woke up with bad headache, winded, vomited, diaherra (as reported), coughing. On 23Jan2021, they went to get covid test but due to blood in their nose, they received antibody test which was negative. On 24Jan2021, the patient was still feeling bad with all the above symptoms. Then on 25Jan2021, they went to ENT doctor who cauterized their nose and stated that since antibody was negative to take the maderna vaccine since they have no antibody in their system, the Pfizer vaccine did not work. From 26Jan2021 to 13Feb2021, the patient felt same started feeling better 14Feb2021 but still have sore muscles in their shoulders and cough. The patient underwent lab tests and procedures which included sars-cov-2 antibody test: negative on 23Jan2021.  The action taken in response to the event(s) for bnt162b2 was not applicable. Therapeutic measures were taken as a result of epistaxis and clot blood which include the doctor cauterized their nose. The patient recovered with sequel from the events.; Sender's Comments: Based on available information, a possible contributory role of the subject product, BNT162B2 vaccine, cannot be excluded for the epistaxis and other reported events  due to temporal relationship. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 53 year old man with a past medical history of follicular lymphoma diagnosed in 2008, more recently with DLBCL with CNS involvement (involving hypothalamus; dx 8/2018; s/p HD MTX, s/p BMT- followed by Dr.), autoimmune hepatitis, obesity, adipic DI, central hypothyroidism and type 2 DM who presented to Hospital via EMS after a  fall at home with multisystem organ failure leading to intubation in the ED and subsequent transfer to Oncology ICU for further management.   He was in his usual state if health until Sunday. On Saturday he got COVID vaccine at 4pm, that evening he had no issues. Sunday night around 10pm he didn't make complete sense and his wife was concerned because of his history of DM and treated CNS lymphoma. BG was 320-340 at that time. Monday he was good and Monday night he started to have shaking of his left hand. Tuesday he had one episode of diarrhea. Later he was more shaky in the shower and he started to fall and his wife was unable to grab him and he slid down the wall and could not get up.  Family was called to help and he was not making sense so they called EMS.  Wife reports that he was down approximately 3 hours before EMS was able to get him up. In EMS he was noted to have a large area of skin desquamation from the right posterior knee to the ankle. His GCS was 15. He had stable blood pressure and heart rate. He was hypoxia to the 50s and oxygen was applied.   In the ED he was found to be in multisystem organ failure and was intubated and had rapid progression of shock requiring  Epinephrine, Levophed and Vasopressin. Crash lines were placed and he was sent to hospital.  Upon arrival he was noted to have a cold pulseless right lower extremity and surgery was called. He was evaluated by Trauma Surgery, Orthopedic surgery and Vascular surgery and eventually underwent above the knee amputation. Unfortunately they were not able to remove all nonviable tissue and he continued to deteriorate. He was taken level 1 back to the OR and an additional 10 cm of nonviable tissue was removed. Unfortunately upon arrive he suffered cardiac arrest in the setting of severe lactic acidosis and hyperkalemia.
OTHER_MEDS: Desmopressin levothyroxine Atorvastatin trulicity once a week
CUR_ILL: Hypothyroidism Diabetes Morbid obesity Hyperlipidemia Diabetes insipidus
HISTORY: Diffuse large B Cell lymphoma status post allogeneic BMT 5/3/2019

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I made sure to hydrate and eat well the day of the vaccine. I have had no allergic reactions to any medications/ injections in the past and I was not worried about this one. I didn't take any meds beforehand besides my normal morning modafinil. I have no fear of needles.  I received the vaccine in the auditorium about 1:25pm. The RN did a fantastic job, went through all of the information, no pain at all with the injection. As I was sitting in my chair for monitoring, a few minutes in I began to feel very uncomfortable. I felt clammy/sweaty and kept shifting my weight in my seat. I didn't want to make a big deal of it at first because I worried it was all in my head. But I became more and more uncomfortable. I laid my head down on the little desk, no help. I closed my eyes, no help. About 10 minutes or so in I decided to ask if they had water available. I slowly got up and walked to the back of the room. I couldn't even get the question out of my mouth before the nurse told me to sit down. Apparently I was white as a ghost. They got a wheelchair and wheeled me to the space behind the auditorium. By then I was starting to feel like my throat was closing and I saw spots in my peripheral vision. It was kind of a blur from there. I tried to take deep breaths. I drank a few sips of water and poured some on a paper towel to wet my forehead (and spilled all over my lap because I was a little disoriented at this point). My BP was 60s/40s and then 60s/30s. A rapid response was called. They moved me to a cart flat on my back with my legs elevated. My fingers and toes were starting to go numb and my lips were apparently blue/ white. After laying for a few minutes in Trendelenburg my BP began to resolve and my breathing started to ease a bit. No further intervention was done by the rapid team. I was taken by the Rapid RN to the ED for monitoring. They eventually pushed the cart into a room and took some vitals and an EKG. They had me stand and move to a wheelchair. I felt horrible but improved from before. They had me sit in a wheelchair in the lobby for a few hours before taking me back and placing an IV and drawing labs (I believe it was 3 hours from the initial reaction). I gave a urine sample. They then put me in a wheelchair and wheeled me back into the lobby for some more time. Then, they wheeled me back to a room where they gave some lactated ringers and a PA and MD saw me. By then my BP and breathing was completely resolved. The MD said he wasn't fully convinced it was just a vasovagal episode because I haven't had issues with vaccines in the past and I was well hydrated and my HR was normal. It partly fit the picture for an allergic reaction/ severe immune response d/t the feeling of throat closing, the BP drop, and the elevated WBCs. They advised that I list the vaccine as an allergy and do not get the second dose, especially since I had COVID back in September.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient rec'd vaccine at 1400. She went to wait her 15 minutes in the car and after about 10 minutes noticed eye sensitivity and headache. When symptoms did not pass after an additional 10 minutes she came back into the office. While waiting when her husband was checking her in, she "passed out." Episode lasted less than 1 minute.  She was easily oriented to person, place and time. It was noted that she had some swelling to bilateral eyes. Patient was brought back to room, VS were checked and all were normal. She denied any chest pain, shortness of breath, wheezing, tongue swelling, itching, or tickling sensation to back of the throat. She was able to tolerate sips of water without difficulty. 50mg benadryl IM was given in the left deltoid. Approximately 5 minutes after IM injection patient again "passed out." She was seated at the time and slumped to her right, resting her head on her husband and did not fall from chair. She aroused after approx 2 minutes, and was a/ox4.  VS were rechecked and were O2 99% on RA. HR 101, BP 124/88, RR20, temp 98.5/oral.  Patient stayed at the clinic for an additional 45 minutes after which her eyesight was reported to be back to normal, her headache had improved and the lower eye edema had resolved.   It should be noted that both the patient and the husband were not concerned with her "passing out." She states it happens because of pain and she was fearful of the injections. Patient also states that her neurologist told her that when "she is in too much pain, she will pass out."

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the 8th day following the vaccine, I noticed in the morning that my arm was red in the area of the vaccine site.  Later in the day, it became quite itchy, and then a bit swollen.  The itching went away overnight, and then eventually the redness and swelling went away, probably by the end of the 2nd day.  I hadn't signed up with V-safe, yet, but decided to do that a couple of days after this happened.  I intended to report this symptom on V-safe, but I couldn't figure out how to enter anything after the fact.  I understand now that this has happened to some people, Moderna Arm?!  And the photos I've seen look much like what I had, and the description, in terms of when it started and the how it manifested, was right on target.  I'm not especially concerned about this, but it was odd at the time, and it was good to learn that this has happened to others.  My intent in reporting it is just to help contribute to your understanding of numbers, how many people have experienced this, how often it happens.  If there is a better way to do that, please don't hesitate to let me know!
OTHER_MEDS: Synthroid 100 mcg fish oil Vit D Calcium

Summary - ANAPHYLAXIS. Screened via medical questionnaire with no known hx of anaphylaxis after receiving injection.  Less than 10 minutes after receiving injection, pt's son reported to staff that pt was overheated and not feeling well. After receiving ice water, pt became non-responsive to questions and developed tongue swelling, blocked airway and audible wheezing. 0.3mg IM epinephrine injected into L thigh. Pt was laid down in empty exam room. Blood pressure 130/80, pulse 96, temp 96.9. Pt able to sit up, answer questions and breathe comfortably without distress within few minutes of receiving epinephrine. Examined by EMS and declined transportation to ER. Called by physician 4 hours later; pt reported doing well.

There was a significant drug interaction with Efudex Cream that I was applying topically to a pre-cancerous 2-cm-diameter lesion on my left shin. On the day of my first Pfizer shot, the Efudex treated lesion was progressing normally from the desquamation (scabbing and shedding of epithelial scales) to the erosion stage (starting to form a shallow 2.5-cm-diameter ulcer). Starting about Saturday 30 January (three days after the first Pfizer shot) and slowly increasing for the next four days, the Efudex-treated ulcer became deeper, the peripheral 12-cm-diameter skin became redder, and the left foot and ankle became increasingly swollen.  My RN-wife and I (a former medical-research physicist) began research andChronic health conditions: nasal polyps, precancerous bleeding actinic keratoses, Cramp-Fasciculation Syndrome (leg & foot cramps), early macular degeneration bilateral, hearing loss bilateral. Chronic health conditions: nasal polyps, precancerous bleeding actinic keratoses, Cramp-Fasciculation Syndrome (leg & foot cramps), early macular degeneration bilateral, hearing loss bilateral.DVERSE EFFECTS, TREATMENT, AND OUTCOME:  discovered that Efudex should not be given concurrently with any of a long list of immunizations.  This is an Efudex problem that should gain another immunization onto that list. Being within a week of finishing the Efudex regimen, we monitored the Efudex-treatment area and the peripheral area carefully. On Thursday 4 Feb (eight days after the first Pfizer shot), the ulcer began unusual drainage, the 12-cm-diameter peripheral area became inflamed, and swelling of the left ankle and foot increased to almost skin-tight - I can upload photos if you need.  Time for immediate action.  My excellent Dermatologist stopped Efudex and started me on Bactrim by mouth for 10 days, and Gentamicin topical antibiotic on the ulcerated central area and Triamcinolone topical corticosteroid on the peripheral and swollen areas for three weeks.  Good choices.  Improvement was immediate and continued improving for the next three weeks.  By the time of the second Pfizer shot on 24 February, the central area was healing well, in the late-reepithelialization stage (regrowth of epithelial tissue that now formed a completely-covering scar tissue with no oozing), and with all inflammation and swelling completely gone.  After the second Pfizer shot (taken 20 days after stopping Efudex), there were zero adverse effects of any kind. NOTE: There were absolutely zero other adverse effects of any kind throughout the entire series: no chills, fever, headache, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, change in pulse or blood pressure (120/70 range), loss of taste or smell, sore throat, cough, lung congestion, fatigue, feeling of being unwell, shortness of breath, injection-site swelling or redness, hives, swelling of face, decreased kidney function, or other adverse cardiovascular, neurological or pulmonary effects. There was no additional joint pain above my normal osteoarthritis.  After both shots, I felt a slight normal-range injection-site soreness for the next few hours, but no site swelling, rash, redness, or other problem.  We recommend that this immunization be added to the Efudex  �proscribed or warned' list.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About an hour after the shot, I felt some tingling in my face; that was followed by a few odd sensations, all of which are basically the same as when I have a flu shot.  Eight hours after the shot, I noticed that I was smelling smoke; my sense of smell started to do weird things an hour before (for example, smelling rotten food in the fridge), but this became clear when the smoke smell started.  Over the first 48 hours, my left arm was sore (sore to touch at 24 hours, gone at 48), and I had some mild flu symptoms (sore throat, stuffy nose, fatigue), plus some chest "tightness" which I have been feeling from time to time since March 2020.  The flu-like symptoms were all basically gone except the stuffy nose.  I still have a slight stuffy nose, and the strange smell issue.  I have been able to smell things fine all along, it's just overlaid with a smell that started as smoke or BBQ, and varies in strength; it's a bit like smelling dirt now.  It's always possible this is coincidental, but I wasn't exposed to smoke or anything that I think could cause my nose to go haywire.
LAB_DATA: None, my doctor didn't think there was anything to worry about when I emailed her.
HISTORY: In March 2020, I caught something (no one knows what) which caused some fluid to appear in my lungs; my lungs presented with the "broken glass" appearance in an X-ray, though that was largely gone 12 days later in a CT.  There are still pockets in the very edges of my bronchioles that show up under a CT scan; with the pandemic I have not been willing to have a biopsy done to determine what is in there.  I was not tested for COVID in March, and did not have antibodies in November; no one has an explanation for what this is.  After I am fully vaccinated we will do a biopsy and maybe figure it out finally.
PRIOR_VAX: In 2018 the flu shot gave me Occular Response syndrome for 24-48 hours; my eyes had trouble focusing and I had severe chills and
ALLERGIES: Allergic to erythromyacin (led to Stevens Johnson syndrome 35 years ago).  Slight allergy to shellfish.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: COVID-19 VACCINE - Patient received 1st dose of Moderna on 2/2/21.   Was scheduled to receive 2nd dose on 3/3/21.   Pfizer vaccine was administered in error on 3/3/21 as second dose.       No symptoms reported by patient's husband on 3/5/21.
Clinician reconstituted with 0.8 instead of 1.8 cc saline

At approximately 930 am, Offender was vaccinated in Housing Unit and returned to his bed. He was monitored by nursing staff for 15 minutes and had no adverse reaction or side effects. At approximately 1030am, Offender  was called to the officer's desk and was told to report to the visiting room for vaccination. Upon arrival, offender  was again vaccinated in the opposite arm. Offender was called in error rather than his room mate was who was an add on to the vaccination list. Offender was admitted to the Health Care Unit for observation for 24 hrs. Vital signs remained stable throughout this period with only a complaint of bilateral sore arms.  There were nono additional sequelae. Office of Health Services was notified of the incident on February 25, 2021 and began a review as part of our quality improvement process and in order to recommend practice modifications, provide education, implement policy change, monitor outcomes and prevent re-occurrence.  OHS reviewed information obtained from Moderna regarding the management of vaccine administration errors.  The error at facility is known as an "invalid dose".  In general there is limited information, yet low risk, for individuals who either receive a second dose within 21 days or a higher than authorized dose volume. The recommendations in this guidance related to the facility occurrence are summarized:  Second dose administered in < 21 days  Do not repeat dose. Higher than authorized dose volume administered  Do not repeat dose. * � Inform the recipient of the potential for local and systemic adverse.    Additional recommendations from the process:   1. Identity verification.  There were several opportunities for Health Care Staff, Security Staff, and  Guardsmen to confirm the identify of Offender. a. All offenders must wear their ID throughout all steps of the vaccination process.   b. Health Care Staff, Security Staff, andGuardsmen must verify offender identities as needed for their assignments throughout each step the vaccination process c. Health care staff must verify accurate completion of offender vaccination forms and ensure that forms match the offender being vaccinated.  d. Health care and Security staff must identify offenders by offender name and number rather than housing assignment. e. Use of handwritten lists should be minimized.  Other pre-printed available rosters or spreadsheets are preferable 2. Offender completed two sets of consent forms for vaccination.  It is unclear if he did not understand the process, or exactly why he would repeat the vaccination process.   a. Though language did not appear to be an issue, appropriate interpreters should be made available to obtain consents and provide education. b. When necessary consent forms should be provided in the native language spoken by the offender. c. It is unclear why there was no further attempt to confirm that Offender had previously received a vaccination that day, after stating that fact to those present before he received his second dose of vaccine. In the future, if an individual states that he or she has already been vaccinated the process must stop until his or her claims have been verified or shown to be false. 3. Any unplanned changes to the onsite vaccination plan (add-ons, extra dose redistribution, team deployment etc.) must be communicated to all members of the vaccination team.  4. Health care staff alone are responsible for the completion of all consent forms and vaccination documentation.   5. Identify best practices and standardize vaccination add-ons across facilities. Consider: location, addition to master vaccination roster, etc. a. Perhaps add-on vaccinations can be moved to another area for tracking. b. Add-ons should be added to the master vaccination roster.  Additional recommendations: 6. Re-Training on the vaccination protocol for health care, operations and national guard staff.    The above items were completed.
LAB_DATA: CBC and CMP were ordered and drawn 2-26-21.

Patient's parents were on-site and were advised of the error, there was no concern expressed by the parents. Patient was observed for 15 minutes and no reactions were noted. At 5 days post vaccination, patient developed severe left shoulder pain, originally thought to be secondary to chronic shoulder pain and a recent fall, over the next three days it progressed to swelling, severe pain, and limited ROM. He ended up being admitted to the hospital and CT scan showed development of significant soft tissue infiltration around sternum and sternoclavicular joints. This was originally thought to be infectious, but he never developed a fever or leukocytosis and we feel this was most likely an inflammatory process. I have no idea if this was actually a vaccine side effect, but given the proximity in both time a location and the known complication of shoulder pain with the vaccine, it seems reasonable to give you the information to monitor for other similar cases.

Received vaccine on 3/3/21 at 2:30pm. Waited for 20 minutes at pharmacy for allergic reaction. Given the all clear, so headed home. Around 5pm, I started noticing how extremely sore my left arm was, almost as if somebody had hit it with a baseball bat (no bruising, redness, etc., just VERY sore). I also started noticing numbness and tingling in my left arm that traveled down the outside of my arm into my left hand and into my left pinky finger.   As the evening progressed, I lost my appetite, developed a headache, felt extremely fatigued, was dizzy, had muscle and joint aches, had left kidney pain, and began to feel flushed and hot. I took my temperature and it showed I was running a low-grade fever of 98.7F (my normal temperature is anywhere between 96.9F and 97.1F). I went to bed around 9pm.  Around 3am (which is now 3/4/21), I woke up with nausea, and my left arm/hand/finger really experiencing numbness and tingling (it's as if that portion of my arm/hand/finger was semi-paralyzed). I went to the bathroom and was on the verge of throwing up. I broke out into a cold, clammy sweat but did not vomit. I got back into bed and went back to sleep.  Around 5am (still 3/4/21), I woke up again with nausea and my left arm/hand/finger still numb and tingling (semi-paralyzed). I went to the bathroom and was again on the verge of throwing up. I, again, broke out into a cold, clammy sweat but did not vomit. I got back into bed. I decided to take a Zofran around 6am for the nausea.  I slept from 8am-12pm on 3/4/21 due to the Zofran. When I woke up, I called the pharmacist at pharmacy to notify them of my symptoms. The pharmacist everything I experienced was normal and should go away in 2-3 days (if they didn't then contact my regular doctor), that I could take Tylenol for any pain, and I still needed to keep my follow-up appointment for the second shot.  The entire day on 3/4/21 from 12pm until I went to bed around 10pm, I still experienced an extremely sore arm, loss of appetite, slight headache, fatigue, dizziness, muscle and joint aches, left kidney pain, low-grade fever (for me), and the numbness/tingling/paralysis in my left hand and left pinky finger.  I was able to sleep through the night, and woke up around 6am on 3/5/21. Currently, I am still experiencing an extremely sore arm, fatigue, and the numbness/tingling/paralysis in my left hand and left pinky finger. I am EXTREMELY concerned about the numbness/tingling/paralysis in my left hand and left pinky finger as it does not seem to be getting better.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Friday, February 18th, 2021, patient received Moderna COVID-19 vaccine in the left deltoid administered by Pharm D at our pharmacy. The patient called the pharmacy on March 4th, 2021 to explain that her arm was red and itchy.  The pharmacist that day told the patient to use ice compresses and to come by the pharmacy to show us her reaction.   Today, March 5th, the patient came to the pharmacy with her son to show us her left deltoid. I observed her arm was red and hot to the touch. She has very defined edges of the rash on her arm. She did not have streaking on her arm, that I observed.  Patient said she had a small, red spot about 3 days after she received the shot, which started February 21st .  She was complaining of itching and has been watching the red spot get bigger every day. I instructed her to call you to have you look at her arm. She said it was just itching and she would like to try OTC products before going to the doctor.  I instructed her to take Benadryl 25mg up to four times per day.  Because Benadryl will make her tired, she can only take it when she is at home and not driving.  I also gave her Hydrocortisone 1% ointment to use at least twice per day on her arm.  I also reiterated that ice packs would help with the redness and discomfort.  She verbalized her understanding. I instructed her to call you to make an appointment if she is not improving. I also told her if she sees any signs of continued spreading or red streaks on her arm, she needs to seek immediate medical attention.
